info.author: Mark Dufour
info.description: Shed Skin is an experimental (restricted-)Python-(2.x)-to-C++ compiler. It accepts pure but implicitly statically typed Python (2.4-2.6) programs and generates optimized C++ code. The result can be further compiled to stand-alone programs or extension modules.
info.keywords: compile compiler c c++ speed slow optimize psyco pypy pyrex cython rpython
info.name: Shed-Skin
